<paragraph blockId="6.[177,1085,1378,1596]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">
C o m m e n t: The original description is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus box="[996,1085,1379,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Elisabethpol&quot; (REITTER 1884). An examination of the type series in the Reitter collection at the HNHM, which comprises 
<specimenCount box="[613,730,1434,1456]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" type="male">eight males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[779,893,1434,1456]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
, revealed that they belong to two species, so that a 
<typeStatus box="[510,603,1462,1484]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation is mandatory in the interest of the stability of nomenclature. Two males are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(KORGE)" baseAuthorityName="Korge" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[800,1079,1490,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turkestanicum">
<emphasis box="[800,978,1490,1512]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">O. turkestanicum</emphasis>
(KORGE)
</taxonomicName>
. One of the males that are not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Korge" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[686,865,1518,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turkestanicum">
<emphasis box="[686,865,1518,1540]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">O. turkestanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[177,273,1546,1568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The interpretation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter, Hozman" authorityYear="1884" box="[515,645,1546,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cryptobium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egregium">
<emphasis box="[515,645,1546,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">O. egregium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="ZANETTI A" box="[692,857,1546,1568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" pagination="31 - 41" refId="ref20787" refString="ZANETTI A. (1980): Contributo alla conoscenza delle specie italiane del genere Cryptobium MANNH., con note sulle specie europee e del Caucaso. - Lavori - Societa Veneziana di Scienze Naturali 5: 31 - 41." type="journal article" year="1980">ZANETTI (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="HOZMAN P" box="[915,1084,1546,1568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" pagination="311 - 322" refId="ref20514" refString="HOZMAN P. (1985): Beitrag zur Kenntnis westpalaarktischer Arten der Gattung Cryptobium MANNHEIM [sic] (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 92: 311 - 322." type="journal article" year="1985">HOZMAN (1985)</bibRefCitation>
refers to an undescribed species, which is described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" box="[733,886,1574,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="permutatum">
<emphasis box="[733,886,1574,1596]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="403">O. permutatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[177,1085,219,328]" pageId="7" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="REITTER" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[177,424,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egregium">
<emphasis box="[177,424,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="404">Ochthephilum egregium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ponto-Mediterranean" baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[740,846,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collare">
<emphasis box="[740,846,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="404">O. collare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other similar congeners by the distinctly smaller aedeagus and the shape of its internal structures (Figs 8- 10, 20-21). The forebody of all examined specimens is of more or less uniformly brownish coloration.
</paragraph>
